items.title: Coca-Cola bottlers to invest Rs 25,760 crore in India's food processing sector
items.description: SLMG Beverages, Coca-Cola's largest bottler in India, will contribute Rs 8,000 crore to the investment

items.title: Starbucks to close stores, cut jobs in $1 billion restructuring
items.description: Starbucks  News: The company said its overall store count will drop by 1% during the 2025 fiscal year, ending with 18,300 total locations across the US and Canada.

items.title: Lawmakers seek answers from major US firms over H-1B visa use amid layoffs: Report
items.description: The report comes after the Trump administration said last week it would ask companies to pay $100,000 per year for H-1B visas

items.title: EU opens probe into possible anticompetitive practices by SAP
items.description: The commission said SAP is seen to have distorted competition in the market for maintenance and support services for its Enterprise Resource Planning software.

items.title: PE major Warburg Pincus looks to raise Rs 4,000 crore in debt for Haier India stake buy
items.description: People aware of the matter said the exclusivity period is currently on and that a formal announcement is expected in the coming weeks. The plan is for the Mittal-Warburg consortium to acquire a 49 percent stake, with Haier retaining another 49 percent and employees holding the remaining 2 percent.

items.title: Hinduja flagship kicks off China tie-up with battery-making goal
items.description: Ashok Leyland’s collaboration with a Chinese cell-making behemoth, if successful, could serve as a test case for some of the largest Indian conglomerates.

items.title: Nothing spins off CMF as independent subsidiary, forms $100 mn mfg JV with Optiemus
items.description: As part of this transition, Nothing and Indian electronics major Optiemus Infracom have formed a strategic joint venture to establish India as a global production and export base for Nothing and CMF products.

items.title: Jinkushal Industries IPO: A low-margin exporter at a high-multiple valuation
items.description: The IPO proceeds to be used to meet operating needs rather than for progression

items.title: Alibaba, Nvidia show market is instantly rewarding AI spending
items.description: Other stocks that’ve seen a lift this year after pledging to spend more than $317 billion combined on AI include Meta Platforms Inc., Microsoft Corp, Alphabet Inc. and Amazon.com Inc., whose gains account for a major part of the S&P 500 Index’s rally in 2025.

items.title: Intel is seeking an investment from Apple as part of its comeback bid
items.description: A deal with Apple, a longtime Intel customer that switched to in-house processors in the past five years, would represent further validation of the chipmaker’s turnaround bid.
